productsMIB.name: productsMIB

revisions.description: This is the Exalt Products mib. rev:1.01

productsMIB.contactinfo: Exalt Communication Inc. 254 E Hacienda Ave., Campbell, CA 95008 USA

radioInfo.name: radioInfo
radioInfo.description: Common Radio Information to all Exalt devices.

modelName.name: modelName
modelName.description: A descriptive name for the Radio. See Web, Radio Information, Model Name.

partNumber.name: partNumber
partNumber.description: The Part Number of the Radio. See Web, Radio Information, Part Number.

serialNumber.name: serialNumber
serialNumber.description: The Radio Serial Number. See Web, Radio Inforamtion, Serial Number.

interfaceType.name: interfaceType
interfaceType.description: The Interfaces available on this radio. Ethernet, T1/E1, etc. See Web, Radio Information, Interface Type.

firmwareVersion.name: firmwareVersion
firmwareVersion.description: The Radio Firmware Version. See Web, Radio Information, Firmware Version.

bootVersion.name: bootVersion
bootVersion.description: The Radio Boot Code Version. See Web, Radio Information, Boot Version.

rdkDbVer.name: rdkDbVer
rdkDbVer.description: The Device RDK Database Version. See Web, Radio Information, RDK Database Version.

txFreqRange.name: txFreqRange
txFreqRange.description: The Radio Tx Frequency Range. FDD radios have a Tx and Rx frequency range. See Web, Radio Information, RF Transmit range. TDD radios have one frequency range. See Web, Radio Information, RF Frequency Band.

rxFreqRange.name: rxFreqRange
rxFreqRange.description: The Radio Rx Frequency Range. FDD radios have a Tx and Rx frequency range. See Web, Radio Information, RF Receive range. TDD radios have one frequency range. See Web, Radio Information, RF Frequency Band.

rfFreqBand.name: rfFreqBand
rfFreqBand.description: The Device Frequency Band (Range). TDD radios have N/A value in this field. FDD radios have TX High or TX Low depending on used diplexer and Transmit frequency. See Web, Radio Information, Tx Band.

hwId.name: hwId
hwId.description: The Device Hardware ID number. See Web, Radio Information, Hardware ID number

modelNumber.name: modelNumber
modelNumber.description: The Model Number of the Radio. See Web, Radio Information, Model Number

sysDate.name: sysDate
sysDate.description: The Radio System Date, MM/DD/YYYY. See Web, Administration, Settings, Date. To make permanent, write save to commitAdminSettings after change. After commit, SNMP restarts and will be down for 30 seconds.

sysTime.name: sysTime
sysTime.description: The Radio System Time, HH:MM:SS, as 24 hours. See Web, Administration, Settings, Time. To make permanent, write save to commitAdminSettings after change. After commit, SNMP restarts and will be down for 30 seconds.

rnLocal.name: rnLocal
rnLocal.description: The user specifiable Radio Name for this radio. See Web, Administration, Settings, Radio Name. To make permanent, write save to commitAdminSettings after change.

rnRemote.name: rnRemote
rnRemote.description: The Radio Name of the Radio at the far end of this RF Link. Can only be set at that radio. See Web, Administration, Settings, Radio Name.

linkName.name: linkName
linkName.description: The user specifiable Link Name for this radio. See Web, Administration, Settings, Link Name. To make permanent, write save to commitAdminSettings after change.

linkSecKey.name: linkSecKey
linkSecKey.description: The Link Security Key must match on both ends of an RF Link for traffic to pass. See Web, Administration, Settings, Link Security Key. To make permanent, write save to commitAdminSettings after change.

adminPassword.name: adminPassword
adminPassword.description: The password for admin login to Web/CLI. See Web, Administration, Settings, Admin Password. To make permanent, write save to commitAdminSettings after change.

userPassword.name: userPassword
userPassword.description: The password for user login to Web/CLI. See Web, Administration, Settings, User Password. To make permanent, write save to commitAdminSettings after change.

ipLocal.name: ipLocal
ipLocal.description: The IP address of local radio. This IP address is used to manage radio. See Web, Administration, Settings, IP Address. To make permanent, write save to commitAdminSettings after change.

ipRemote.name: ipRemote
ipRemote.description: The IP address of the remote Radio. This IP address is used to manage Remote radio. Can only be set at that radio. See Web, Administration, Settings, IP Address.

subnetMask.name: subnetMask
subnetMask.description: The Subnet Mask for IP address of local radio. See Web, Administration, Settings, IP Mask. To make permanent, write save to commitAdminSettings after change.

ipAddressNetmask.name: ipAddressNetmask
ipAddressNetmask.description: The IP address and Subnet Mask of local radio. ie 10.0.0.1/24. To make permanent, write save to commitAdminSettings after change.

defaultGateway.name: defaultGateway
defaultGateway.description: The Default Gateway for local radio port. See Web, Administration, Settings, Default Gateway. To make permanent, write save to commitAdminSettings after change.

aesEnable.name: aesEnable
aesEnable.description: The AES enable(0)/disable(1). AES (Advance Encryption Standard) can be implemented to provide additional data security for the wireless link. This function requires an upgrade license key (purchased separately). See Web, Administration, Settings, AES Settings, Enable AES. To make permanent, write save to commitAdminSettings after change.

aesKey.name: aesKey
aesKey.description: The symmetric AES key for encrypt/decrypt payload data. Different bitlength encryption license keys (for example, 128-bit and 256-bit) are available, depending on model type and license type. AES Key should match both on local radio and far end radio. See Web, Administration, Settings, AES Settings, AES Key. To make permanent, write save to commitAdminSettings after change.

licKey.name: licKey
licKey.description: The license key which defines radio features and capabilities. See Web, Administration, Settings, License Key. To make permanent, write save to commitAdminSettings after change.

trapIpaddr.name: trapIpaddr
trapIpaddr.description: The IP address to which the SNMP traps are directed. See Web, Administration, SNMP, Traps, Trap Destination IP Address.

trapAuth.name: trapAuth
trapAuth.description: Authentication trap enable(1)/disable(0). This is an SNMP standard trap when password information for SNMP is incorrect. See Web, Administration, SNMP, Traps, Authentication Trap.

trapReboot.name: trapReboot
trapReboot.description: Reboot trap enable(0)/disable(1). This trap is sent after any radio reboot to inform the manager of the reboot status. See Web, Administration, SNMP, Traps, Radio Reboot Trap.

trapLocLinkStat.name: trapLocLinkStat
trapLocLinkStat.description: Local Link Status trap enable(0)/disable(1). This trap is sent when Link is in errored state (equivalent to the Link LED). See Web, Administration, SNMP, Traps, Local Link Status Trap.

trapLocAlarmStat.name: trapLocAlarmStat
trapLocAlarmStat.description: Local Alarm Status trap enable(0)/disable(1). This trap is sent when local radio Status is in errored state (equivalent to the Status LED). See Web, Administration, SNMP, Traps, Local Radio Status Trap.

trapRemAlarmStat.name: trapRemAlarmStat
trapRemAlarmStat.description: Remote Alarm Status trap enable(0)/disable(1). This trap is sent when remote radio Status is in errored state (equivalent to the Status LED). See Web, Administration, SNMP, Traps, Remote Radio Status Trap.

trapLocRslStat.name: trapLocRslStat
trapLocRslStat.description: Local RSL Status trap enable(0)/disable(1). This trap is sent when the local RSL drops below the value set in the RSL Threshold Value (dBm) field. See Web, Administration, SNMP, Traps, Local RSL Status Trap.

trapLocTempStat.name: trapLocTempStat
trapLocTempStat.description: Local Temperature Status trap enable(0)/disable(1). This trap is sent when the internal temperature reaches the warning point. See Web, Administration, SNMP, Traps, Temperature Status Trap.

trapLocRslThreshold.name: trapLocRslThreshold
trapLocRslThreshold.description: Local RSL Threshold. Exalt recommends that this trap be set to a value 5dBm or 10dBm above the threshold as a warning that the system has faded and may be approaching an outage. See Web, Administration, SNMP, Traps, Threshold Value.

trapv1Enable.name: trapv1Enable
trapv1Enable.description: SNMPv1 Traps enable(0)/disable(1). Enables traps for SNMP protocol version 1. See Web, Administration, SNMP, Traps, Enable SNMPv1 Traps.

trapv2cEnable.name: trapv2cEnable
trapv2cEnable.description: SNMPv2c Traps enable(0)/disable(1). Enables traps for SNMP protocol version 2c. See Web, Administration, SNMP, Traps, Enable SNMPv2c Traps.

trapv3Enable.name: trapv3Enable
trapv3Enable.description: SNMPv3 Traps enable(0)/disable(1). Enables traps for SNMP protocol version 3. See Web, Administration, SNMP, Traps, Enable SNMPv3 Traps.

ntpClientEnable.name: ntpClientEnable
ntpClientEnable.description: this mib to enable/disable the NTP client in the radio. 0 - disable NTP client. 1 - enable with 1 NTP server. 2 - enable with 2 NTP servers. 3 - enable with 3 NTP servers. 4 - enable with 4 NTP servers.

ntpServer1IpAddr.name: ntpServer1IpAddr
ntpServer1IpAddr.description: IP address for the first NTP server in xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx format

ntpServer2IpAddr.name: ntpServer2IpAddr
ntpServer2IpAddr.description: IP address for the second NTP server in xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx format

ntpServer3IpAddr.name: ntpServer3IpAddr
ntpServer3IpAddr.description: IP address for the third NTP server in xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx format

ntpServer4IpAddr.name: ntpServer4IpAddr
ntpServer4IpAddr.description: IP address for the forth NTP server in xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx format

ntpTimeZoneSelect.name: ntpTimeZoneSelect
ntpTimeZoneSelect.description: Time Zone selection. 0 - (GMT-11:00) Samoa 1 - (GMT-10.00) Hawaii 2 - (GMT-09:00) Alaska 3 - (GMT-08:00) Pacific Time 4 - (GMT-07:00) Arizona 5 - (GMT-07:00) Montain Time 6 - (GMT-06:00) Central Time 7 - (GMT-05:00) Eastern Time 8 - (GMT-05:00) Indiana (East) 9 - (GMT-04:00) Atlantic Time (Canada) 10- (GMT) Coordinated Universal Time 11- (GMT) London 12- (GMT+01:00) Berlin 13- (GMT+01:00) Belgrade 14- (GMT+01:00) Paris 15- (GMT+02:00) Cairo 16- (GMT+02:00) Helsinki 17- (GMT+03:00) Baghdad 18- (GMT+03:00) Moscow 19- (GMT+03:30) Tehran 20- (GMT+04:30) Kabul 21- (GMT+05:00) Karachi 22- (GMT+07:00) Bangkok 23- (GMT+08:00) Shanghai 24- (GMT+08:00) Taipei 25- (GMT+09:00) Tokyo 26- (GMT+09:00) Seoul 27- (GMT+10:00) Sydney 28- (GMT+10:00) Vladivostok

commitNtpSettings.name: commitNtpSettings
commitNtpSettings.description: This command allows saving or clear the NTP and Tome Zone configuration. If the save includes the change of time zone, the radio will automatically reboot to take effect the newly selected time zone. Option strings to be written are: save, clear, correspondingly saving changes to configuration to the persistent storage or clearing unsaved changes.

commitAdminSettings.name: commitAdminSettings
commitAdminSettings.description: The Commit Administration settings command. Valid values: 'save', 'clear'. Configuration changes via SNMP do not take effect until 'save' (Commit) command is sent to this parameter. 'clear' (Cancel) command is used to cancel configuration changes before commit operation. In case of invalid configuration this parameter contains text description of the problem.

systemConfig.name: systemConfig
systemConfig.description: This is the device specific configuration section.

commitSystemSettings.name: commitSystemSettings
commitSystemSettings.description: The Commit System Configuration settings command. Valid values: 'save', 'clear'. Configuration changes via SNMP do not take effect until 'save' (Commit) command is sent to this parameter. 'clear' (Cancel) command is used to cancel configuration changes before commit operation. In case of invalid configuration this parameter contains text description of the problem.

te1.name: te1
te1.description: T1,E1 interfaces Configuration section. Section allows to configure T1/E1 ports on the radio if any.

te1NumChannels.name: te1NumChannels
te1NumChannels.description: The Number of T1 or E1 channels supported by the Radio.

te1NumActiveChannels.name: te1NumActiveChannels
te1NumActiveChannels.description: The Current number of channels available, based on bandwitdh of the RF link and the license key.

selectT1orE1.name: selectT1orE1
selectT1orE1.description: Select operation mode of T1/E1 interfaces. Either T1(0) or E1(1). See Web, Configuration, Interface, T1/E1, Set To E1/T1 Mode button.

te1Interfaces.name: te1Interfaces
te1Interfaces.description: Attributes for T1 or E1 ports.

te1Interface.name: te1Interface
te1Interface.description: An entry in the T1/E1 Attribute table.

te1Status.name: te1Status
te1Status.description: The T1/E1 status: enable(1)/disable(0). Parameter allows to enable/disable each individual T1 channel. See Web, Configuration, Interface, T1/E1, Status. To make permanent, write save to commitTe1Settings after change.

t1LBO.name: t1LBO
t1LBO.description: The Line Build Out length range. Valid values (ft): lbo0to133(0), lbo133to266(1), lbo266to399(2), lbo399to533(3), lbo533to655(4). See Web, Configuration, Interface, T1/E1, LBO. To make permanent, write save to commitTe1Settings after change.

te1AIS.name: te1AIS
te1AIS.description: The T1/E1 AIS enabled flag: enable(1)/disable(0). If enabled, the radio places an AIS code on the output of the associated interface if and when the link fails or when there is no E1 signal available from the far end to provide the user at the local end. See Web, Configuration, Interface, T1/E1, AIS. To make permanent, write save to commitTe1Settings after change.

t1LineCode.name: t1LineCode
t1LineCode.description: The T1/E1 Line Code type: b8zs(0), ami(1). See Web, Configuration, Interface, T1/E1, AIS, Line Code. To make permanent, write save to commitTe1Settings after change.

te1LoopBackMode.name: te1LoopBackMode
te1LoopBackMode.description: The Loop Back Mode for a T1/E1 interface. Valid values: disabled(0), ExternalLocal(1), ExternalRemote(2), Internal(3). All loopback configurations control the loop at the Line Interface integrated circuit, which is the device wired directly to the front panel ports. See Web, Configuration, Interface, T1/E1, AIS, Loopback. To make permanent, write save to commitTe1Settings after change.

commitTe1Settings.name: commitTe1Settings
commitTe1Settings.description: The Commit TE1 Configuration settings command. Valid values: 'save', 'clear'. Configuration changes to TE1 ports via SNMP do not take effect until 'save' (Commit) command is sent to this parameter. 'clear' (Cancel) command is used to cancel configuration changes before commit operation. In case of invalid configuration this parameter contains text description of the problem.

fileManagement.name: fileManagement
fileManagement.description: The File Management Section. This section allows to initiate Upload/Download firmware/configuration/logs, perform Firmware activation procedure.

currentFwFilename.name: currentFwFilename
currentFwFilename.description: The file name of the currently running firmware. See Web, Administration, File Management, File Activation, Current File.

alternateFwFilename.name: alternateFwFilename
alternateFwFilename.description: The file name of the alternate firmware image. See Web, Administration, File Management, File Activation, Alternative File.

swapFWimage.name: swapFWimage
swapFWimage.description: Swap the firmware images and restart radio. To perform swap operation 'swap' command needs to be sent to this parameter. For ExtendAirG2 to perform revert to factory operation 'factory' command needs to be sent. Radio will become unavailable for several minutes.

fileTransfer.name: fileTransfer
fileTransfer.description: The File Transfer Section. This section allows to initiate Upload/Download firmware/configuration/logs over TFTP protocol.

factoryFwFilename.name: factoryFwFilename
factoryFwFilename.description: The file name of the factory firmware image. See Web, Administration, File Management, File Activation, Factory File.

uploadFilename.name: uploadFilename
uploadFilename.description: The name of the file for upload operation. For configuration file uploadFilename should be always 'config.xml'. uploadFilename value should match the file name in TFTP server folder.

transferType.name: transferType
transferType.description: The file transfer type. Valid values: - uploadFirmware(0) - uploadConfig(1) - uploadRDD(2) (Valid only for TDD radios) - downloadFirmware(3) - downloadConfig(4) - downloadMIBs(5) - downloadEventLogs(6). The actual operation starts via updating transferStart parameter value.

transferStart.name: transferStart
transferStart.description: TransferStart parameter is used to initiate file transfer operation. Send startTransfer(1) to this parameter.

locLinkState.name: locLinkState
locLinkState.description: The Link Status Alarm. Possible values: - almNORMAL(0) - Error-free connection (BER<10e-6) - almMINOR(1) - Errorred connection (BER<10e-3) - almMAJOR(2) - No link (BER>10e-3) See Web, Monitor, Alarms, Link

locTempAlarm.name: locTempAlarm
locTempAlarm.description: The Temperature Alarm state. Possible values: - almNORMAL(0) - Normal temprature range - almMINOR(1) - Exceeding normal temprature range See Web, Monitor, Alarms, Temperature

locCurrentTempS.name: locCurrentTempS
locCurrentTempS.description: The Internal Temperature as a string.

locLinkSecMismatch.name: locLinkSecMismatch
locLinkSecMismatch.description: This is link security mismatch alarm. This alarm tells if the Link Security Key is matching or not. Possible values: - almNORMAL(0) - Link Secutiry keys match - almMAJOR(2) - Link Secutiry keys do not match

locTe1LinkSummary.name: locTe1LinkSummary
locTe1LinkSummary.description: The T1/E1 Link Summary LED color.

locTe1Alarm.name: locTe1Alarm
locTe1Alarm.description: The Alarms state for the Local T1/E1 Channel. Possible values: - almNORMAL(0) - Enabled and connection present - almMAJOR(2) - Enabled and no connection present - almDisable(3) - Disabled and no connection present - almNotAvailable(4) - T1/E1 channel is not available See Web, Monitor, Alarms, T1/E1 Input

remLinkState.name: remLinkState
remLinkState.description: The Link Status Alarm for far end radio. Possible values: - almNORMAL(0) - Error-free connection (BER<10e-6) - almMINOR(1) - Errorred connection (BER<10e-3) - almMAJOR(2) - No link (BER>10e-3) - almNotAvailable(4) - Telemetry is down See Web, Monitor, Alarms, Link

remTempAlarm.name: remTempAlarm
remTempAlarm.description: The Temperature Alarm state for far end radio. Possible values: - almNORMAL(0) - Normal temprature range - almMINOR(1) - Exceeding normal temprature range - almNotAvailable(4) - Telemetry is down See Web, Monitor, Alarms, Temperature

remCurrentTemp.name: remCurrentTemp
remCurrentTemp.description: The Internal Temperature in Celsius for far end radio.

remCurrentTempS.name: remCurrentTempS
remCurrentTempS.description: The internal Temperature as a string for far end radio.

remLinkSecMismatch.name: remLinkSecMismatch
remLinkSecMismatch.description: This is link security mismatch alarm. This alarm tells if the Link Security Key is matching or not. Possible values: - almNORMAL(0) - Link Secutiry keys match - almMAJOR(2) - Link Secutiry keys do not match - almNotAvailable(4) - Telemetry is down

remTe1LinkSummary.name: remTe1LinkSummary
remTe1LinkSummary.description: The T1/E1 Link Summary LED color.

remTe1Alarm.name: remTe1Alarm
remTe1Alarm.description: The Alarms state for the Local T1/E1 Channel of far end radio. Possible values: - almNORMAL(0) - Enabled and connection present - almMAJOR(2) - Enabled and no connection present - almDisable(3) - Disabled and no connection present - almNotAvailable(4) - Telemetry is down or T1/E1 channel is not available See Web, Monitor, Alarms, T1/E1 Input

locCurrentBER.name: locCurrentBER
locCurrentBER.description: The Curent Bit-Error Rate as scaled integer for local radio. The BER multiplied by 1,000,000. If the link is operating perfectly, this should indicate zero. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Current BER

locCurrentBERstr.name: locCurrentBERstr
locCurrentBERstr.description: The Current Bit-Error Rate as a string.

locCurrentRSL.name: locCurrentRSL
locCurrentRSL.description: Current RSL is the measurement of the received signal level. When the RSL falls below the threshold specification, the link disconnects and will not reconnect until the RSL is above the threshold specification. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Current RSL

locCurrentRSLstr.name: locCurrentRSLstr
locCurrentRSLstr.description: The Current RSL as a string.

locErrorDuration.name: locErrorDuration
locErrorDuration.description: The Error Duration indicates the total number of seconds that occurred where there was at least one bit error since the last time that the radio statistics counter was reset. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Errored Seconds

locErrorDurationStr.name: locErrorDurationStr
locErrorDurationStr.description: The Error Duration as a formatted string.

locUnavailDuration.name: locUnavailDuration
locUnavailDuration.description: Unavailable Duration keeps track of every second where the BER equals or exceeds 1x10-3, as well as any seconds where there is a complete loss of radio communication. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Unavailable Seconds

locUnavailDurationStr.name: locUnavailDurationStr
locUnavailDurationStr.description: The Unavailable Duration as a formatted string.

locMinRSL.name: locMinRSL
locMinRSL.description: The Minimum RSL indicates the worst (lowest) received signal level that occurred since the last counter reset. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Minimum RSL

locMinRSLstr.name: locMinRSLstr
locMinRSLstr.description: The Minimum RSL value as a string.

locMinRSLtimestamp.name: locMinRSLtimestamp
locMinRSLtimestamp.description: The Minimum RSL Timestamp indicates the date and time when the Minimum RSL occurred. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Minimum RSL Timestamp

locMaxRSL.name: locMaxRSL
locMaxRSL.description: The Maximum RSL indicates the best (highest) RSL that occurred since the last counter reset. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Maximum RSL

locMaxRSLstr.name: locMaxRSLstr
locMaxRSLstr.description: The Maximum RSL level As string.

locSampleDuration.name: locSampleDuration
locSampleDuration.description: The Sample Duration indicates the amount of time passed since the last counter reset. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Time Since Reset

locSampleDurationStr.name: locSampleDurationStr
locSampleDurationStr.description: The Sample Duration value as a formatted string.

locEthPerfInterfaces.name: locEthPerfInterfaces
locEthPerfInterfaces.description: Performance characteristics of local Ethernet interfaces

locEthPerfInterfacesEntry.name: locEthPerfInterfacesEntry
locEthPerfInterfacesEntry.description: An entry in the Performance characteristics of local Ethernet interfaces table

locEthUtilizationIn.name: locEthUtilizationIn
locEthUtilizationIn.description: Inbound ethernet utilization (%). See Web, Analysis, Ethernet Utilization.

locEthUtilizationOut.name: locEthUtilizationOut
locEthUtilizationOut.description: Outbound ethernet utilization (%). See Web, Analysis, Ethernet Utilization.

locEthUtilizationWatermarkEnabled.name: locEthUtilizationWatermarkEnabled
locEthUtilizationWatermarkEnabled.description: Ethernet utilization watermark enable(1)/disable(0). See Web, Analysis, Ethernet Utilization, Ethernet Utilization Watermark.

locEthUtilizationWatermark.name: locEthUtilizationWatermark
locEthUtilizationWatermark.description: Ethernet utilization watermark level (%). See Web, Analysis, Ethernet Utilization, Watermark level.

locEthUtilizationWatermarkTrapEnabled.name: locEthUtilizationWatermarkTrapEnabled
locEthUtilizationWatermarkTrapEnabled.description: Ethernet utilization watermark trap enable(1)/disable(0). The watermark trap function allows administrators to receive an SNMP trap when watermark conditions are exceeded. See Web, Analysis, Ethernet Utilization, Enable Ethernet Utilization Trap.

locEthUtilizationWatermarkTrapDuration.name: locEthUtilizationWatermarkTrapDuration
locEthUtilizationWatermarkTrapDuration.description: Ethernet utilization trap limit in minutes/day (0-1440 minutes). See Web, Analysis, Ethernet Utilization, Send trap if watermark hit duration exceeds.

locMaximumTxModulation.name: locMaximumTxModulation
locMaximumTxModulation.description: The highest/maximum Tx modulation when ACM is enabled since the last counter reset. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Tx modulation.

locActiveTxModulation.name: locActiveTxModulation
locActiveTxModulation.description: The active Tx modulation when ACM is enabled. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Tx modulation.

locMinimumTxModulation.name: locMinimumTxModulation
locMinimumTxModulation.description: The lowest/minimum Tx modulation when ACM is enabled since the last counter reset. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Tx modulation.

locMaximumRxModulation.name: locMaximumRxModulation
locMaximumRxModulation.description: The highest/maximum Rx modulation when ACM is enabled since the last counter reset. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Rx modulation.

locActiveRxModulation.name: locActiveRxModulation
locActiveRxModulation.description: The active Rx modulation when ACM is enabled. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Rx modulation.

locMinimumRxModulation.name: locMinimumRxModulation
locMinimumRxModulation.description: The lowest/minimum Rx modulation when ACM is enabled since the last counter reset. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Rx modulation.

locMaximumTxEthernetThroughput.name: locMaximumTxEthernetThroughput
locMaximumTxEthernetThroughput.description: The highest/maximum Tx Ethernet throughput in Mbps when ACM is enabled since the last counter reset. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Tx Ethernet Throughput.

locActiveTxEthernetThroughput.name: locActiveTxEthernetThroughput
locActiveTxEthernetThroughput.description: The active Tx Ethernet throughput in Mbps when ACM is enabled. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Tx Ethernet Throughput.

locMinimumTxEthernetThroughput.name: locMinimumTxEthernetThroughput
locMinimumTxEthernetThroughput.description: The lowest/minimum Tx Ethernet throughput in Mbps when ACM is enabled since the last counter reset. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Tx Ethernet Throughput.

locMaximumRxEthernetThroughput.name: locMaximumRxEthernetThroughput
locMaximumRxEthernetThroughput.description: The highest/maximum Rx Ethernet throughput in Mbps when ACM is enabled since the last counter reset. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Rx Ethernet Throughput.

locActiveRxEthernetThroughput.name: locActiveRxEthernetThroughput
locActiveRxEthernetThroughput.description: The active Rx Ethernet throughput in Mbps when ACM is enabled. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Rx Ethernet Throughput.

locMinimumRxEthernetThroughput.name: locMinimumRxEthernetThroughput
locMinimumRxEthernetThroughput.description: The lowest/minimum Rx Ethernet throughput in Mbps when ACM is enabled since the last counter reset. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Rx Ethernet Throughput.

locResetStats.name: locResetStats
locResetStats.description: Write 'reset' to locResetStats to clear the Performance statistics.

remCurrentBER.name: remCurrentBER
remCurrentBER.description: The Curent Bit-Error Rate as scaled integer for far end radio. The BER multiplied by 1,000,000. If the link is operating perfectly, this should indicate zero. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Current BER

remCurrentBERstr.name: remCurrentBERstr
remCurrentBERstr.description: The Current Bit-Error Rate as a string. Far end radio

remCurrentRSL.name: remCurrentRSL
remCurrentRSL.description: Current RSL is the measurement of the received signal level. When the RSL falls below the threshold specification, the link disconnects and will not reconnect until the RSL is above the threshold specification. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Current RSL

remCurrentRSLstr.name: remCurrentRSLstr
remCurrentRSLstr.description: The Current RSL as a string.

remErrorDuration.name: remErrorDuration
remErrorDuration.description: The Error Duration indicates the total number of seconds that occurred where there was at least one bit error since the last time that the radio statistics counter was reset. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Errored Seconds, Remote column.

remErrorDurationStr.name: remErrorDurationStr
remErrorDurationStr.description: The Error Duration as a formatted string. Far end radio.

remUnavailDuration.name: remUnavailDuration
remUnavailDuration.description: Unavailable Duration keeps track of every second where the BER equals or exceeds 1x10-3, as well as any seconds where there is a complete loss of radio communication. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Unavailable Seconds

remUnavailDurationStr.name: remUnavailDurationStr
remUnavailDurationStr.description: The Unavailable Duration as a formatted string. Far end radio.

remMinRSL.name: remMinRSL
remMinRSL.description: The Minimum RSL indicates the worst (lowest) received signal level that occurred since the last counter reset. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Minimum RSL, Remote column.

remMinRSLstr.name: remMinRSLstr
remMinRSLstr.description: The Minimum RSL value as a string. Far end radio.

remMinRSLtimestamp.name: remMinRSLtimestamp
remMinRSLtimestamp.description: The Minimum RSL Timestamp indicates the date and time when the Minimum RSL occurred. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Minimum RSL Timestamp, Remote column.

remMaxRSL.name: remMaxRSL
remMaxRSL.description: The Maximum RSL indicates the best (highest) RSL that occurred since the last counter reset. See Web, Monitor, Performance, Maximum RSL, Remote column.

remMaxRSLstr.name: remMaxRSLstr
remMaxRSLstr.description: The Maximum RSL level As string. Far end radio.

remSampleDuration.name: remSampleDuration
